properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 27 at 7:02PM PST until January 29 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Wind Advisory, northeast winds 20 to 30 mph
with gusts up to 55 mph expected. For the High Wind Watch,
northeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 65 mph possible.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...For the Wind Advisory, until 3 AM PST Tuesday. For the
High Wind Watch, from Tuesday evening through Wednesday
evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel
could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways 101 and 154 will be affected
with the strongest winds in the Montecito Hills, San Marcos
Pass, and Gaviota/Refugio areas.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.
